- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper analyzes the views of Twitter users and examines the polarization among the general public.
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is also a likely category as the paper may involve the use of software tools for data collection and analysis.
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is another possible category as the paper may involve natural language processing techniques for analyzing the content of tweets and hashtags.
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is a possible category as the paper examines the political polarization among the general public and its impact on society.
- cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences) is another possible category as the paper analyzes the behavior and characteristics of Twitter users who support or oppose Kavanaugh's nomination.
